# Documentation maintenance

Before exploring the codebase from scratch, read:
- `docs/INDEX.md` — navigation hub
- `docs/repo-map.md` — where modules and scripts live
- `docs/schema/README.md` — tables and data flow
- `docs/experiments/README.md` — experiment docs layout

## Update docs in the same PR when you change:

| Change | Update |
|--------|--------|
| `Config` defaults or model mechanics | `docs/model.md` |
| `DDL` in `website/build/build_db.py` or new DuckDB column | `docs/schema/duckdb.md` |
| SQL against `public.*` (columns, joins, filters) | `docs/schema/postgres.md` |
| `CACHE_VERSION_NPZ`, npz keys, `RatingResults` fields | `docs/schema/cache.md` |
| `venue_overlay/store.py` DDL | `docs/schema/venue-overlay.md` |
| `rating_api/pg_state.py` or overlay tables | `docs/schema/api-overlay.md` |
| New top-level package or major script group | `docs/repo-map.md` |
| `Config` default or promoted/rejected experiment | `docs/experiments/experiments_summary_ru.md` + doc under `docs/experiments/` |
| New website route | `docs/repo-map.md` (website section) |

## Do not duplicate

- Model math and hyperparameter defaults stay in `docs/model.md`.
- Experiment details stay under `docs/experiments/` (not in `docs/` root).
- Schema docs describe **columns and relationships**, not business logic.

## Schema source of truth

Code wins over markdown. If docs and code disagree, fix the docs (or fix the code if the bug is in code).
